SIMPLE: mum
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mum
<hw>Mum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Of imitative origin. Cf.
<er>Mumble</er>.]</ety> <def>Silent; not speaking; <as>as, to keep
<ex>mum</ex></as>.</def> <rj><au>Thackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The citizens are <qex>mum</qex>, and speak not a word.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>mum's the word</b></col> <cd>keep this a secret; don't
tell anybody.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mum</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mum
<hw>Mum</hw>, <pos>interj.</pos> <def>Be silent! Hush!</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Mum</qex>, then, and no more.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mum</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Mum
<hw>Mum</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Silence.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Hudibras.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mum</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Mum
<hw>Mum</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G. <ets>mummere</ets>, fr. Christian
<ets>Mumme</ets>, who first brewed it in 1492.]</ety> <def>A sort of
strong beer, originally made in Brunswick, Germany.</def>
<rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The clamorous crowd is hushed with mugs of <qex>mum</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mumble</ent>⟦br⟧
